## 2026-05-05 ‚Äî HMR singleton guards + missing deps + test coverage (243/243)

**Branch:** `fix/landlord-launch-blockers`

### What shipped

#### Context singleton guards (all 5 context files)
- Added `window.__mde*Context` singleton pattern to `useAuth.tsx`, `TripContext.tsx`, `ThreePanelContext.tsx`, `OnboardingContext.tsx`, `MapContext.tsx`
- Prevents blank-page crash when Vite HMR caches a module at two different `?t=<timestamp>` URLs ‚Äî both instances share the same context object via `window`, eliminating the "used outside Provider" throw
- `vite.config.ts` server headers changed from `no-store` ‚Üí `no-cache` so the browser can be primed with fresh module bytes while still using the cache normally in production

#### Missing npm deps installed
- `qrcode` + `@types/qrcode` ‚Äî used by `src/pages/me/TicketDetail.tsx` (QR code display)
- `posthog-js` ‚Äî used by `src/lib/posthog.ts` (analytics)
- `@googlemaps/markerclusterer` ‚Äî used by `src/components/chat/ChatMap.tsx`
- `jsqr` ‚Äî used by `src/hooks/useScanner.ts` (QR scanner)
- `fake-indexeddb` ‚Äî required by `src/lib/scanQueue.test.ts` (offline scan queue tests)
- `@testing-library/dom` ‚Äî peer dep for `@testing-library/react`

#### L8 confirmed + test added
- `Step1Address.tsx` already implements the manual fallback: "Can't find your address?" link sets `manualFallback=true` ‚Üí Continue button enabled without lat/lng (server-side geocode handles missing coords)
- Added `Step1Address.test.tsx` scenario: clicks manual fallback, verifies Continue is enabled without coordinates

