**048 sponsor-stripe-checkout** (`supabase/functions/sponsor-checkout/index.ts`, `supabase/functions/sponsor-payment-webhook/index.ts`)
- Creates Stripe Checkout session for sponsor packages; webhook confirms payment + flips `applications.status='active'`
- ‚öÝÔ∏è Needs `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` + `STRIPE_SPONSOR_WEBHOOK_SECRET` + `FRONTEND_URL` secrets in Supabase dashboard
- ‚öÝÔ∏è Needs `sponsor-assets` storage bucket created in Supabase dashboard

**049 sponsor-surface-component** (`src/components/sponsor/SponsoredSurface.tsx`)
- `<SponsoredSurface placementId="..." surface="contest_header" />` renders brand logo + UTM link
- Fires impression on mount; fires click on user interaction
- **C3 bug fixed:** Tailwind `ease-[cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)]` ‚Üí `ease-in-out` (commas inside `[]` confuse JIT parser)

**050 sponsor-impression-click-edge-fns** (`supabase/functions/sponsor-impression/index.ts`, `supabase/functions/sponsor-click/index.ts`)
- Impression: upserts `sponsor.impressions` row; idempotent on `(placement_id, viewer_anon_id, day)`
- Click: writes `sponsor.clicks` with `viewer_user_id` (JWT-resolved when auth header present) ‚Äî **C1 fix**
- ‚öÝÔ∏è M2 open: impression fn still doesn't capture `viewer_user_id` for logged-in users

**051 sponsor-attribution-trigger** (`supabase/migrations/20260504081937_sponsor-attribution-trigger.sql`)
- `sponsor.attribute_order()` trigger on `event_orders` INSERT/UPDATE
- Last-click 24h attribution: matches `viewer_user_id` or `viewer_anon_id` ‚Üí writes `sponsor.attributions`
- Attribution failure never blocks order INSERT (EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS ‚Üí WARNING)
- **Applied to prod ‚úÖ** (2026-05-04 via MCP)

**052 sponsor-dashboard** (`src/pages/sponsor/SponsorDashboard.tsx`, `src/hooks/useSponsorDashboard.ts`)
- CPM/CPC/CPA KPI tiles pulling from `sponsor.roi_daily`
- Attribution funnel chart (impressions ‚Üí clicks ‚Üí conversions)

**053 sponsor-roi-rollup-cron** (`supabase/migrations/20260504082006_sponsor-roi-rollup-cron.sql`)
- `sponsor.rollup_roi_daily()` aggregates impressions + clicks + attributions ‚Üí `roi_daily` for `CURRENT_DATE`
- pg_cron every 5 minutes; idempotent ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE
- **C2 bug fixed:** added `cron.unschedule` before `cron.schedule` so re-running migration doesn't create duplicates
- **Applied to prod ‚úÖ** (2026-05-04 via MCP)

**H1 fix ‚Äî UNIQUE constraint** (`supabase/migrations/20260504090000_sponsor-orgs-contact-unique.sql`)
- `ALTER TABLE sponsor.organizations ADD CONSTRAINT orgs_contact_unique UNIQUE (primary_contact_user_id)`
- Without this, `upsert onConflict:"primary_contact_user_id"` in `sponsor-application-create` silently fell back to INSERT, creating orphan org rows per wizard session
- **Applied to prod ‚úÖ** (2026-05-04 via MCP)

### Critical bugs fixed inline (commit `1409e27`)

| # | File | Bug | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| C1 | `sponsor-click/index.ts` | `viewer_user_id` never written ‚Üí attribution trigger's logged-in buyer path could never match | Added JWT resolution; inserts `viewer_user_id` when auth header present |
| C2 | `sponsor-roi-rollup-cron.sql` | No `cron.unschedule` before `cron.schedule` ‚Üí duplicate cron jobs on migration re-run | Added idempotent `DO $$ BEGIN PERFORM cron.unschedule(...) EXCEPTION ... END $$` |
| C3 | `RightDetailPanel.tsx` | `ease-[cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)]` commas confuse Tailwind JIT ‚Üí wrong/missing easing in prod | Replaced with `ease-in-out` (identical curve, unambiguous) |

