**034 event-staff-link-generator** ([supabase/functions/event-staff-link-generator/index.ts](supabase/functions/event-staff-link-generator/index.ts) + [supabase/functions/_shared/jwt.ts](supabase/functions/_shared/jwt.ts))
- Mints HS256 staff-link JWTs signed with dedicated `STAFF_LINK_SECRET` (audit M2 ‚Äî separate from Supabase JWT secret)
- 24h default TTL, max 168h (7 days), Zod-validated
- Companion `revoke: true` body branch bumps `events.staff_link_version` via service_role-only RPC
- New shared helper `_shared/jwt.ts` (Web Crypto API, no third-party JOSE; alg-confusion guarded; key cache; exp/nbf with 30s clock skew)
- Migration `20260503091256_event_staff_link_revocation.sql` with `bump_staff_link_version(uuid)` RPC + REVOKE PUBLIC + GRANT service_role
- **Tests:** 3/3 boundary curl matrix (METHOD/auth/revoke) + RPC smoke test (1‚Üí2 verified)
- Advisor count: ‚àí2 (RPC properly locked to service_role only)

**004 ticket-checkout** ([supabase/functions/ticket-checkout/index.ts](supabase/functions/ticket-checkout/index.ts))
- Stripe Checkout session + atomic capacity via `ticket_checkout_create_pending` RPC
- Pre-mints attendee UUIDs in JS, signs QR JWTs with those UUIDs, then INSERTs (audit R6 ‚Äî JWT.attendee_id always == row PK)
- Stripe metadata only carries `{order_id}` ‚Äî no PII, no attendees array (audit B1)
- Order persists `ticket_id` + `quantity` so webhook knows what to finalize (audit B2)
- Idempotency cache via existing `idempotency_keys` table (only success cached; failures retry deterministically)
- Stripe failure ‚Üí calls `ticket_checkout_cancel` RPC to release capacity immediately
- **Tests: 12/12 pass** ‚Äî 8 HTTP boundary (METHOD, INVALID_PAYLOAD √ó3, ATTENDEES_MISMATCH, quantity bounds, CONFIG_ERROR, idempotency replay) + 4 RPC (happy path, OUT_OF_STOCK, cancel, finalize)
- Phase 1 = COP only (CHECK constraint enforces); USD/MXN extension is a 1-line currency lookup

**005 ticket-payment-webhook** ([supabase/functions/ticket-payment-webhook/index.ts](supabase/functions/ticket-payment-webhook/index.ts))
- Stripe signature verification via `constructEventAsync` (uses raw body ‚Äî no JSON re-parse mid-verify)
- Idempotency on `event.id` (Stripe retries up to 3 days on 5xx; deduped via existing table)
- `payment_intent.succeeded` ‚Üí `ticket_payment_finalize` RPC (audit R4 ‚Äî single transaction: order flip + attendees flip + qty transfer)
- `charge.refunded` ‚Üí looks up order by `stripe_payment_intent` + calls `ticket_payment_refund` (audit R5 ‚Äî handles `string | object | null` correctly)
- ORDER_NOT_FOUND / ORDER_BAD_STATE ‚Üí log + swallow (200, no Stripe retry); other errors ‚Üí 500 (Stripe retries)
- SendGrid email is best-effort; absence of `SENDGRID_API_KEY` skips silently ‚Äî buyers retrieve tickets via /me/tickets
- **Tests: 3/3 boundary curl matrix** (full Stripe sig path requires real keys; deferred until secrets set, but RPC chain it calls is verified by 004 test #12)

**006 ticket-validate** ([supabase/functions/ticket-validate/index.ts](supabase/functions/ticket-validate/index.ts))
- Staff JWT verification with `STAFF_LINK_SECRET` (in-function ‚Äî `verify_jwt = false` per audit B4 because tokens are custom HS256, not Supabase user JWTs)
- QR JWT verification with `QR_SIGNING_SECRET` (separate secret per security-by-isolation)
- Cross-checks: `staff.event_id === scanner_event_id`, `qr.event_id === scanner_event_id`, `staff.staff_link_version === events.staff_link_version` (revocation gate)
- Atomic single-use via `ticket_validate_consume` RPC (race-safe `UPDATE ... WHERE qr_used_at IS NULL RETURNING`)
- Distinguishes `INVALID_SIGNATURE` (counterfeit) from `UNKNOWN_TOKEN` (refunded/cancelled/sync race) per audit medium issue
- **Audit log on every scan** (success or failure) ‚Üí `event_check_ins` table for forensic + oversell post-mortem
- HTTP 200 for app-level outcomes (consumed/already_used/etc) so scanner branches on `error.code`; HTTP 4xx only for transport failures
- **Tests: 4/4 HTTP boundary** + 3/3 RPC outcomes (consumed ‚Üí already_used on rescan + unknown_token + audit log insert)

