**A4 ‚Äî Tighten `Conversation.user_id` to `(string & {}) \| 'anon'`** ([src/types/chat.ts](src/types/chat.ts))
- New exported type alias `ConversationUserId = (string & {}) | 'anon'` with extensive JSDoc explaining:
  - The `string & {}` no-widening trick preserves `'anon'` IntelliSense autocomplete while still accepting any UUID.
  - The contract: never insert `'anon'` into FKs to `auth.users`, never subscribe to realtime channels with anon owner, etc.
  - The bug class this prevents: previously `anon-${sid}` was once stored on `messages.conversation_id` (uuid type) and threw at runtime ‚Äî the 'anon' marker now lives ONLY on `user_id` and the type makes that explicit.
- Closes **R8**.

**A6 ‚Äî `viewport_idle` event reaches PostHog** ([src/lib/maps-telemetry.ts](src/lib/maps-telemetry.ts), [src/lib/posthog.ts](src/lib/posthog.ts), [src/lib/sentry.ts](src/lib/sentry.ts), [src/components/chat/ChatMap.tsx](src/components/chat/ChatMap.tsx))
- Was already fired as a maps-telemetry event ‚Üí Sentry breadcrumb. Now also forwarded to PostHog with `bboxN/S/E/W` floats + `zoom`. Answers "which neighborhoods do users dwell on the longest?" without per-pin telemetry.
- Extended `MapTelemetryEvent.viewport_idle` to include `zoom` (1‚Äì22 from `map.getZoom()`). Updated the ChatMap idle listener to populate it.
- Added `viewport_idle` arm to the `AppEvent` discriminated union in `posthog.ts`.
- Added the forwarder branch in `mapEventToSentry()` (`sentry.ts`) ‚Äî same shape pattern as `pin_click` / `cluster_expand` / `auth_failed`. Closes **R12**.

